#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:2
#: 3f180a02e4c0443986623a78c9d1b697
msgid "Hertzian Contact"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:4
#: 057dc0c0baf846a2821cdc9f7f14147e
msgid ""
"A 2D contact-mechanics problem: a circular elastic indenter is pressed "
"into a rectangular elastic block; the contact pressure along the "
"interface should match the analytical Hertz solution. The script "
"``examples/solid/hertzian_contact/hertzian_contact.py`` solves it with a "
"**penalty method** — the contact constraint is enforced by adding a "
"quadratic penalty energy to the total potential, then minimized with "
"L-BFGS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:14
#: e6c003a8f93242febd78ee408c6370ec
msgid "Problem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:16
#: 1e17c83681244e96b3223a904f87a6c4
msgid "Two linear-elastic bodies (:math:`E = 1000` Pa, :math:`\\nu = 0.3`):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:18
#: aec9ff594b294057ba42dfe34497f6e0
msgid ""
"**Indenter** — full circular disc of radius :math:`R = 1.0`, meshed with "
"Tri6 quadratic triangles, centered at :math:`(-1.0, 0)` so the right-most"
" point sits at the origin. Its left-most arc (:math:`x < -1.8`) is "
"clamped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:22
#: 1c7ab793a72a4985b86d99d74f465682
msgid ""
"**Block** — rectangle :math:`[0, 1] \\times [-1, 1]`, meshed with Quad9 "
"quadratic quadrilaterals. The right edge (:math:`x = 1`) has prescribed "
"displacement :math:`u_x = -0.15` (pushing left, into the indenter)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:27
#: 7dc499b92f7946fb808a416d1dbf79d5
msgid ""
"The contact interface is the vertical line :math:`x = 0`. As the block "
"moves leftward the indenter is compressed, and a contact patch forms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:33
#: 77b5e87d20fc4c37a17fb2e2dc2faba5
msgid "Penalty contact"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:35
#: ca82db0cb8764950b352b9497019c7fd
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Frictionless normal contact is the constraint :math:`g(\\mathbf{x}) \\geq"
" 0`, where :math:`g` is the **gap function** (signed distance between the"
" two surfaces, positive when separated). The penalty method replaces the "
"inequality constraint by the contact energy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:41
#: 3ae03b1f17d24d93ade0a8ad171dfc32
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"E_\\text{contact}\n"
"\\;=\\;\n"
"\\frac{1}{2}\\, k_p \\int_{\\Gamma_c}\n"
"\\langle -g \\rangle_+^2 \\,\\mathrm{d}\\Gamma,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:48
#: 8ab4f17718154f7ebe07257098c0da45
msgid ""
"where :math:`\\langle x \\rangle_+ = \\max(x, 0)` and :math:`k_p = 2 "
"\\times 10^6` is the penalty stiffness. As :math:`k_p \\to \\infty` the "
"constraint is enforced exactly, but the problem becomes ill-conditioned; "
"in practice :math:`k_p` is chosen to be a few orders of magnitude larger "
"than the elastic stiffness."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:55
#: 486271efb785474d94abdf189265d7ef
msgid "The total energy minimized at each L-BFGS step is"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:57
#: f19ac9ab00b8416096e461cd9893a681
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\Pi(\\mathbf{u})\n"
"\\;=\\;\n"
"\\int_{\\Omega_1} \\tfrac12 \\boldsymbol{\\varepsilon}_1 : \\mathbb{C} : "
"\\boldsymbol{\\varepsilon}_1\n"
"\\;+\\;\n"
"\\int_{\\Omega_2} \\tfrac12 \\boldsymbol{\\varepsilon}_2 : \\mathbb{C} : "
"\\boldsymbol{\\varepsilon}_2\n"
"\\;+\\;\n"
"E_\\text{contact}."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:67
#: 7f1690adfd33418fb706f21708bd1ce3
msgid ""
"The first two terms come from "
":class:`~tensormesh.LinearElasticityElementAssembler` 's energy form "
"(small-strain quadratic energy); the contact term is implemented "
"separately in the script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:74
#: f70cba0b905e4dc9a43fbf55eef61011
msgid "Point-to-segment detection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:76
#: 6e5ba925be8e43688321bf2e5abcbf46
msgid ""
"The interface :math:`\\Gamma_c` is partitioned into \"slave nodes\" on "
"one body and \"master segments\" on the other. For each slave node, the "
"script projects onto the closest master segment, computes the signed "
"normal gap, and accumulates the penalty contribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:81
#: 9867077ee7af447fb9d25f733152e627
msgid ""
"The script does this **two-way** (each body's interface nodes are slaves "
"with respect to the other body) which gives a symmetric formulation and "
"avoids the bias of a one-master-one-slave choice."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:87
#: e097c40382c94de69814ef5fa2e2103c
msgid "Energy minimization with L-BFGS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:89
#: e43bde5f36e74fdebe95fed8582dc933
msgid ""
"The pattern is the one introduced in :doc:`hyperelastic_beam`: a single "
"``u`` parameter for both meshes, BCs enforced inside the closure, "
"autograd providing the gradient. The contact term is re-evaluated every "
"iteration because the gap function depends on the current configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:95
#: cbb4467203b3440785a0d4cf37f79c4d
msgid "examples/solid/hertzian_contact/hertzian_contact.py (sketch)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:113
#: 9e1840bab9164a59b887fdc315544845
msgid "Comparison with the Hertz analytical solution"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:115
#: 9288eb946c244d83b6860095f724a169
msgid ""
"For 2D plane-strain contact between an elastic cylinder and a half-space,"
" Hertz theory gives a parabolic pressure distribution:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:118
#: dd3ee1723581434bba0fbc28688c5f89
msgid ""
"p(x) \\;=\\; p_\\text{max}\\, \\sqrt{1 - (x / a)^2},\n"
"\\qquad\n"
"p_\\text{max} = \\sqrt{\\frac{P\\, E^*}{\\pi\\, R^*}},\n"
"\\qquad\n"
"a = \\sqrt{\\frac{4 P\\, R^*}{\\pi\\, E^*}},"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:126
#: 377e0180fd434c6cb766057e85bf47e4
msgid ""
"with effective modulus :math:`E^*` and effective radius :math:`R^*` "
"derived from the two-body geometry. The script extracts the contact "
"pressure from the converged solution and overlays it on the analytical "
"curve in ``hertzian_contact.png`` — the FEM match is good once the mesh "
"is fine enough near the contact patch (``chara_length=0.1`` is a "
"reasonable starting point)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:133
#: 08c9f90f3e044ece9fc3f233b9a0bdf7
msgid "Hertzian contact von Mises stress field"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/hertzian_contact.rst:137
#: 1242ee05f2c94d44b19681078993a2b6
msgid ""
"Output of ``hertzian_contact.py``: von Mises stress field on the "
"deformable indenter (circle) pressed against the displaced block (right)."
" Stress concentrates in a roughly teardrop-shaped region inside the "
"indenter, centered just inboard of the contact patch — the classical "
"Hertzian subsurface stress distribution. The fixed left wall and "
"prescribed displacement arrows on the right block illustrate the boundary"
" setup."
msgstr ""

